modules.description: Provides routing functionality for an in-memory job queue dashboard, dispatching and queuing jobs with optional delays, and registering jobs for later execution. Operates with web routers, job structures, and context data. Used to build admin interfaces for job management, handle batch job submissions, and manage job registration within a web application.

Provides functions to route a job queue dashboard, dispatch and batch-queue jobs with optional delays, and register jobs for later execution. Operates with web routers, job structures, and context data. Used to integrate a dynamic job management interface into an admin panel and manage asynchronous task execution with transaction support.

Provides routing for a job queue dashboard with customizable scope and back navigation, job dispatching with optional delays and context, bulk job dispatching with transaction support, job registration, and lifecycle management. Operates with web routers, job structures, and context pairs. Used to integrate a dynamic, admin-accessible job management interface with delayed processing and batch job handling.

Provides functions to create, dispatch, and manage background jobs using a queue system. Works with job records containing a type, payload, and metadata. Used to handle long-running tasks like email sending or data exports without blocking HTTP requests.

Routes a job queue dashboard, enabling job dispatching with delays, batch processing, and registration, all integrated with web routers and context data. Supports dynamic admin interfaces for managing job lifecycles, including back navigation and transactional batch operations. Processes individual or bulk jobs, with options to schedule execution and track status through structured job definitions. Examples include submitting delayed tasks, handling asynchronous workflows, and building admin panels for real-time job monitoring.
